		<td><b>Can somebody test some VRC6 code for me? (PowerPak)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've been working on my music tracker, Pornotracker, and I would like to find out if my 6502 player code works on NTSC NES (and/or Famicom). Can somebody try it out on the real deal for me?
<br />
<br />Why wouldn't it work? Well, it writes the sprites manually using $2003/$2004 and I'm not completely sure if that's 100% reliable. It works fine in my PAL NES though.
<br />
<br />I doubt many people have VRC6 dev carts, so you'll need PowerPak with loopy's VRC6 (included in the latest mapper pack).
<br />
<br />Here's the ROM: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://thefox.aspekt.fi/nes/lotus9.nes">http://thefox.aspekt.fi/nes/lotus9.nes</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I know some people are going to run this in an emulator, so let it be known that it only works in Nintendulator and Nestopia. FCEUX and a lot of other emulators don't properly implement VRC6's cycle based IRQ.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


