	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That font's pretty awesome.  What does Locus Curbo Challenge mean exactly?</div>
<br />A 'c' with its upper curve replaced with a horizontal line is a glyph variant of 't', commonly associated with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaelic_type" class="postlink">Gaelic type</a>. You confuse it with 'c'; <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=10423#10423" class="postlink">Dwedit confused it with 'z'</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


